<subSubSection pageId="112" pageNumber="113" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="112.[151,1437,151,1040]" pageId="112" pageNumber="113">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,836,861]" pageId="112" pageNumber="113">Remarks.</emphasis>
This new species differs from 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Evans" baseAuthorityYear="1965" box="[669,856,836,861]" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Anisepyris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="112" pageNumber="113" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pulchripennis">
<emphasis box="[669,856,836,861]" italics="true" pageId="112" pageNumber="113">A. pulchripennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by having the body with dark green reflection and the metapectal-propodeal disc black,; the wings clear hyaline; the antennal scrobe carinate; the ocelli very small; the notaulus very narrow; the metapostnotum with longitudinal ridges; the mesopleural fovea closed; and the mesopleural suture opened, whereas 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Evans" baseAuthorityYear="1965" box="[563,748,943,968]" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Anisepyris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="112" pageNumber="113" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pulchripennis">
<emphasis box="[563,748,943,968]" italics="true" pageId="112" pageNumber="113">A. pulchripennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has the body black; the wings bi-banded; the antennal scrobe ecarinate; the ocelli small; the notaulus narrow; the metapostnotum without longitudinal ridges; the mesopleural fovea opened; and the mesopleural suture closed.
</paragraph>
